sequenceDiagram
    participant Service as Backend Service<br/>(e.g. Cron Job)
    participant AS as Authorization Server
    participant API as Resource Server<br/>(e.g. Internal API)

    Note over Service,API: Client Credentials Grant (RFC 6749 Section 4.4)<br/>Machine-to-machine, no user involved

    rect rgb(232, 245, 233)
        Note over Service: Service authenticates as itself (no user context)
        Service->>AS: POST /token<br/>Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded<br/>Authorization: Basic base64(client_id:client_secret)
        Note right of Service: grant_type=client_credentials<br/>&scope=api:read api:write
    end

    rect rgb(243, 229, 245)
        Note over AS: Validate client credentials
        AS->>AS: Verify client_id and client_secret<br/>Check client is authorized for requested scopes<br/>No consent screen (no user to consent)
        AS-->>Service: 200 OK
        Note right of AS: access_token: eyJhbGciOiJS...<br/>token_type: Bearer<br/>expires_in: 3600<br/>scope: api:read api:write<br/>(NO refresh_token - client can re-authenticate)
    end

    rect rgb(227, 242, 253)
        Note over Service,API: Use access token
        Service->>API: GET /api/data<br/>Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJS...
        API->>API: Validate token<br/>Check scopes include api:read
        API-->>Service: 200 OK with data
    end

    Note over Service,API: Key differences from Authorization Code flow:<br/>1. No user interaction or consent<br/>2. No redirect-based flow<br/>3. No refresh token (just request a new access token)<br/>4. Client IS the resource owner
